<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="C10.S14">
<title>Inequalities; Monotonicity</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C10.S14.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S14.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.14.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E1">|J_{\nu}\left(x\right)|\leq 1, if \nu\geq 0,x\in\mathbb{R}, //// |J_{\nu}\left(x\right)|\leq 2^{-\frac{1}{2}}, if \nu\geq 1,x\in\mathbb{R}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S14.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.14.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E2">0&lt;J_{\nu}\left(\nu\right)&lt;\frac{2^{\frac{1}{3}}}{3^{\frac{2}{3}}\Gamma\left( \tfrac{2}{3}\right)\nu^{\frac{1}{3}}}, if \nu&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S14.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s1">
For monotonicity properties of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.m1">J_{\nu}\left(\nu\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.m2">J_{\nu}'\left(\nu\right)</Math> see Lorch (1992).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.14.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E3">|J_{n}\left(z\right)|\leq e^{|\Im z|}, if n\in\mathbb{Z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.14.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E4">|J_{\nu}\left(z\right)|\leq\frac{|\tfrac{1}{2}z|^{\nu}e^{|\Im z|}}{\Gamma\left (\nu+1\right)}, if \nu\geq-\frac{1}{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s4">
<Math equation-number="10.14.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E5">|J_{\nu}\left(\nu x\right)|\leq\frac{x^{\nu}\exp\left(\nu(1-x^{2})^{\frac{1}{2 }}\right)}{\left(1+(1-x^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}}\right)^{\nu}}, if \nu\geq 0,0&lt;x\leq 1;</Math> see Siegel (1953).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s5">
<Math equation-number="10.14.6" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E6">|J_{\nu}'\left(\nu x\right)|\leq\frac{(1+x^{2})^{\frac{1}{4}}}{x(2\pi\nu)^{ \frac{1}{2}}}\frac{x^{\nu}\exp\left(\nu(1-x^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}}\right)}{\left(1 +(1-x^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}}\right)^{\nu}}, if \nu&gt;0,0&lt;x\leq 1;</Math> see Watson (1944, p. 255).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s6">
For a related bound for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.m3">Y_{\nu}\left(\nu x\right)</Math> see Siegel and Sleator (1954).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s7">
<Math equation-number="10.14.7" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E7">1\leq\frac{J_{\nu}\left(\nu x\right)}{x^{\nu}J_{\nu}\left(\nu\right)}\leq e^{ \nu(1-x)}, if \nu\geq 0,0&lt;x\leq 1;</Math> see Paris (1984).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="8" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.s8">
For similar bounds for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.p2.m4">\mathscr{C}_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> (§10.2(ii)) see Laforgia (1986).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C10.S14.Px1">
<title>Kapteyn’s Inequality</title>    
<para xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.14.8" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E8">|J_{n}\left(nz\right)|\leq\frac{\left|z^{n}\exp\left(n(1-z^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}} \right)\right|}{\left|1+(1-z^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}}\right|^{n}}, if n=0,1,2,\dots,</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p1.m1">(1-z^{2})^{\frac{1}{2}}</Math> has its principal value.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.14.9" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S14.E9">|J_{n}\left(nz\right)|\leq 1, if n=0,1,2,\dots,z\in\mathbf{K},</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p1.m2">\mathbf{K}</Math> is defined in §10.20(ii).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p2.s1">
For inequalities for the function <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p2.m1">\Gamma\left(\nu+1\right)(2/x)^{\nu}J_{\nu}\left(x\right)</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p2.m2">\nu&gt;-\tfrac{1}{2}</Math> see Neuman (2004).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C10.S14.Px1.p3.s1">
For further monotonicity properties see Landau (1999, 2000), and Muldoon and Spigler (1984).
</sentence>

</para>

 
</paragraph>
 
</section>
